Orbit — attribution & provenance
=================================

Orbit is a hackathon project for the Loomi Connect AI Hackathon (Bloomreach).
It composes two third-party components, vendored into this repo (their original
git history was stripped to keep the repo small and to avoid carrying upstream
secrets). Credit and licensing below.

1. hermes/ui/ — Hermes Web UI
   The agent runtime + web UI harness.
   Upstream: https://github.com/nesquena/hermes-webui
   License:  MIT (see hermes/ui/LICENSE)
   Changes:  upstream docs/tests/changelog trimmed; configured for Orbit via
             hermes/.hermes/ (profile, SOUL, Orbit skills, MCP registrations).

2. mcp/bloomreach-engagement-mcp/ — custom Bloomreach Engagement MCP server
   The write-path MCP wrapping the Bloomreach Engagement API (FastMCP/httpx).
   Upstream: https://github.com/Skilux/bloomreach-engagement-mcp
   License:  see upstream repository.

What is original to this project (Orbit team's work)
----------------------------------------------------
- docs/submission/              — hackathon deliverables (summary, architecture,
                                  MCP usage, responsible-AI note, demo script)
- docs/reference/               — supporting docs: scenarios, BR API, MCP mapping
- demo/                         — the interactive demo one-pager (HTML + clips
                                  + voiceover audio)
- agent/                        — the agent's playbook: prompts, skills,
                                  scenario definitions, campaign templates
- hermes/.hermes/profiles/orbit — the Orbit agent profile, SOUL, and the
                                  closed-loop orchestration across MCP surfaces
- docker-compose.yml, README    — packaging and one-command bring-up

Third MCP surface
-----------------
Loomi MCP (read-only, OAuth) is consumed as a remote service, not vendored:
https://loomi-mcp-alpha.bloomreach.com/mcp
